name: Architectural Magazine Photo Style: Better Interior embedding helper (archmagazine)
description:
Inspired by a medium type tag "Architectural Diggest Photo" which is recognized by Stable Diffusion, I researched architectural magazines further and trained this textual inversion to be used as a better version of that medium (example: "archmagazine photo").

Trigger word: archmagazine. Prompt archmagazine photo of or archmagazine 3d render of, etc.

This will help with the composition of the image and will influence colors. It may also navigate toward the Photo medium (data set were photos), but you can always use a strength of 0.5-0.9 if something is too much for you.

It will work best for typical rooms inside the house: Living room, bedroom, bathroom, kitchen, dining room, etc.

Enjoy your image generation and share the results with us in the comments.

modelVersions.name: v1.0
modelVersions.description: trained with 132 images, 50k steps on variable speed
